  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And he cometh to the house of the ruler of the synagogue,.... Along with him, and the three disciples above mentioned; and the Vulgate Latin, Syriac, Arabic, and Persic versions read, \"and they came\", the above persons: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and seeing the tumult; the throng and crowd of people, of relations, friends, neighbours, and acquaintance, on this occasion, all in a hurry, and in one motion or another, expressing their concern by words and gestures. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And them that wept and wailed bitterly; the mourning women, the same with the \"preficae\" of the Romans, who sung mournful songs, and made hideous noises, being hired for this purpose; as also those who played doleful tunes on musical instruments; See Gill on Matthew 9:23. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "And them that wept and wailed bitterly; the mourning women, the same with the \"preficae\" of the Romans, who sung mournful songs, and made hideous noises, being hired for this purpose; as also those who played doleful tunes on musical instruments; See Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 9:23",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
